<p>&#8216;The High Court has backed international firm Taylor Wessing over its refusal to disclose privileged information to the beneficiary of a Bahamian trust. Taylor Wessing was acting for the trustee of the Glennfinnan Settlement when a beneficiary of the trust requested personal data about parties to litigation in the Bahamas.&#8217; </p>
<p><a href="https://www.lawgazette.co.uk/news/firm-right-to-withhold-privileged-information-high-court-rules-/5070370.article">Full Story</a></p><p>Law Society's Gazette, 23rd May 2019</p><p>Source: <a href="https://www.lawgazette.co.uk">www.lawgazette.co.uk</a></p>